1
00:00:10,276 --> 00:00:14,178
<i>[ Waves Crashing ]</i>

2
00:00:19,419 --> 00:00:22,718
<i>[ Wind Howling ]</i>

3
00:00:22,822 --> 00:00:25,723
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>

4
00:00:43,643 --> 00:00:46,168
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>I am Ahmed Ibn Fahdlan,</i>

5
00:00:46,279 --> 00:00:50,045
<i>Ibn Al Abbas, Ibn Rasid,</i>
<i>Ibn Hammad.</i>

6
00:00:50,150 --> 00:00:53,085
<i>And things were</i>
<i>not always thus.</i>

7
00:00:55,455 --> 00:00:58,049
<i>At one time,</i>
<i>I was a poet...</i>

8
00:00:58,158 --> 00:01:01,150
<i>in the greatest city</i>
<i>in the world.</i>

9
00:01:01,261 --> 00:01:05,197
<i>Life was easy,</i>
<i>and I lived without care...</i>

10
00:01:06,433 --> 00:01:08,799
<i>until one fateful day...</i>

11
00:01:08,935 --> 00:01:11,768
<i>I met a beautiful woman...</i>

12
00:01:11,871 --> 00:01:13,998
<i>who belonged to another man.</i>

13
00:01:16,009 --> 00:01:20,002
<i>Herjealous husband</i>
<i>complained to the Caliph...</i>

14
00:01:20,113 --> 00:01:24,413
<i>who made me the ambassador</i>
<i>to the land of the</i> Tossuk Vlad--

15
00:01:24,517 --> 00:01:28,351
<i>a country</i>
<i>far to the north.</i>

16
00:01:28,455 --> 00:01:30,946
<i>I was banished</i>
<i>from my home...</i>

17
00:01:31,057 --> 00:01:33,287
<i>and from all</i>
<i>that I knew.</i>

18
00:01:33,393 --> 00:01:38,660
<i>So, I journeyed by camelback many months</i>
<i>into the lands of barbarian peoples</i>--

19
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:43,065
<i>accompanied by Melchisidek,</i>
<i>an old friend of my father</i>--

20
00:01:43,203 --> 00:01:47,333
<i>through the lands of the Ogus,</i>
<i>the Khazars and the Bulgars,</i>

21
00:01:47,474 --> 00:01:51,171
<i>into the lands of murderous bandits,</i>
<i>called ''Tartars, ''</i>

22
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:54,872
<i>who attack caravans,</i>
<i>slaughtering everyone.</i>

23
00:01:54,981 --> 00:01:57,347
- [ Horse Whinnying ]
- The Tartars are coming !

24
00:01:57,450 --> 00:01:59,645
The Tartars are coming !

25
00:01:59,752 --> 00:02:02,448
<i>The Tartars</i>--

26
00:02:02,555 --> 00:02:06,047
-<i>[ Rumbling ]</i>
-<i>[ Man #2 ] Run! Run for your life!</i>

27
00:02:06,159 --> 00:02:09,060
[ Men Shouting ]

28
00:02:11,197 --> 00:02:14,098
- [ Horse Whinnying ]
- [ Camels Snorting ]

29
00:02:18,238 --> 00:02:20,706
[ Shouting Continues ]

30
00:02:34,220 --> 00:02:36,188
[ Shouting In Native Language ]

31
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:42,292
<i>[ Man ] They have stopped.</i>
<i>They are not following.</i>

32
00:02:42,395 --> 00:02:45,694
-<i>[ Man #2 ] A boat! A boat!</i>
- They're Northmen ! A boat !

33
00:02:45,798 --> 00:02:48,198
<i>A boat! Over there!</i>

34
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:50,996
<i>[ Man #3 ] Look!</i>
<i>They are going!</i>

35
00:02:51,137 --> 00:02:54,402
<i>They are leaving!</i>

36
00:02:54,507 --> 00:02:58,841
Move ! Move !
Keep moving !

37
00:02:58,945 --> 00:03:00,708
Ay-yi-yi-yi-yi-yi.
Wait, wait, wait !

38
00:03:00,813 --> 00:03:03,043
Those men in the boat,
who are they ?

39
00:03:03,149 --> 00:03:06,585
The Northmen.
Keep moving and keep quiet !

40
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:08,620
Why ?
Are they dangerous ?

41
00:03:08,721 --> 00:03:12,953
<i>It depends. Maybe they'll let us go,</i>
<i>or maybe they'll kill us.</i>

42
00:03:13,059 --> 00:03:17,189
[ Shouting ]

43
00:03:17,297 --> 00:03:19,265
<i>[ Ahmed ] I am an ambassador,</i>
<i>damn it!</i>

44
00:03:19,365 --> 00:03:22,163
I am supposed
to talk to people !

45
00:03:22,302 --> 00:03:24,566
You may yet
have the opportunity.

46
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:27,537
<i>[ Shouting Continues ]</i>

47
00:03:34,180 --> 00:03:38,378
What do you suppose the potentate
of this encampment calls himself?

48
00:03:38,484 --> 00:03:40,384
Oh, emperor,
at the very least.

49
00:03:40,486 --> 00:03:42,386
Hmm. Emperor.

50
00:03:42,488 --> 00:03:45,389
-<i>** [ Drums ]</i>
-<i>[ Men Chattering, Laughing ]</i>

51
00:04:02,108 --> 00:04:04,008
We seek your--

52
00:04:05,411 --> 00:04:09,541
We seek your headman,
your king.

53
00:04:12,151 --> 00:04:14,619
Try Greek.

54
00:04:16,823 --> 00:04:18,791
[ Speaking Greek ]

55
00:04:23,730 --> 00:04:25,630
Eh ?

56
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:38,740
[ Speaking Greek ]

57
00:04:44,884 --> 00:04:47,114
[ Speaking Greek ]

58
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:49,882
He says their king
is out there in that tent.

59
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:54,593
He says the king
will not speak to us.

60
00:04:57,430 --> 00:05:01,298
Apparently, the king won't
speak to us because he's dead.

61
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:03,801
<i>This is his funeral.</i>

62
00:05:05,705 --> 00:05:08,401
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]

63
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:14,277
<i>[ Melchisidek ]</i>
<i>You are being introduced to</i>
<i>one of the heirs apparent</i>--

64
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:17,178
-<i>Buliwyf.</i>
-[ Speaking Foreign Language Continues ]

65
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,849
[ Speaking Greek ]

66
00:05:26,859 --> 00:05:29,327
" Buliwyf wishes
a song of glory."

67
00:05:29,395 --> 00:05:32,262
<i>Recite a poem, a tale.</i>

68
00:05:32,365 --> 00:05:34,629
<i>Surely you remember</i>
<i>something.</i>

69
00:05:36,402 --> 00:05:38,302
Uh--

70
00:05:40,907 --> 00:05:43,876
In the beginning,
the Earth was void,

71
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:47,241
-<i>and the spirits of God passed</i>--
- [ Woman Screams ]

72
00:05:50,216 --> 00:05:55,176
- <i>[ People Gasping ]</i>
- <i>[ Body Falls To Floor ]</i>

73
00:05:55,288 --> 00:05:59,190
-<i>[ Chattering, Laughing Resumes ]</i>
-<i>** [ Resumes ]</i>

74
00:06:02,795 --> 00:06:05,457
<i>[ Ahmed Narrating ]</i>
<i>Now that there was a new king,</i>

75
00:06:05,565 --> 00:06:08,625
<i>the Northmen prepared</i>
<i>for the funeral of their old king.</i>

76
00:06:08,768 --> 00:06:12,795
** [ Men Singing In Native Language ]

77
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:15,066
<i>[ Both Speaking Greek ]</i>

78
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:20,077
" We will burn him. In one moment,
he and all he owns can be in paradise.

79
00:06:20,179 --> 00:06:22,079
<i>[ Man Continues In Greek ]</i>

80
00:06:22,181 --> 00:06:26,709
<i>These are our gifts to our lord</i>
<i>to support his kingdom in paradise.</i>

81
00:06:26,819 --> 00:06:30,585
- To take with him ?
- [ Woman Speaking Native Language ]

82
00:06:30,690 --> 00:06:35,093
- <i>[ Man Continues ]</i>
- Lo there do I see my father.

83
00:06:35,194 --> 00:06:37,094
<i>[ Man Continues ]</i>

84
00:06:37,196 --> 00:06:41,758
<i>'Lo there do I see my mother,</i>
<i>my sisters and my brothers.</i>

85
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:45,234
-<i>[ Woman Continues ]</i>
- <i>'Lo there do I see</i>
<i>the line of my people...</i>

86
00:06:45,338 --> 00:06:48,307
-<i>back to the beginning.</i>
-<i>[ Man Continues ]</i>

87
00:06:48,441 --> 00:06:51,205
'Lo they do call to me.

88
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:54,575
<i>They bid me take my place among them</i>
<i>in the halls of Valhalla,</i>

89
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:57,342
where the brave
may live forever.

90
00:06:57,450 --> 00:07:01,011
-<i>[ Man Continues ]</i>
-<i>[ Melchisidek ]</i>
<i>''She will travel with him.</i>

91
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:04,647
<i>You will not see this again.</i>
<i>It is the old way. ''</i>

92
00:07:31,317 --> 00:07:34,650
<i>[ Men Chattering In Native Language ]</i>

93
00:07:59,245 --> 00:08:02,009
[ Groaning ]

94
00:08:05,117 --> 00:08:08,450
Another ship arrived
during the night.

95
00:08:08,554 --> 00:08:12,183
There's a boy standing out there
on the bow like he's a statue.

96
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:15,192
[ Speaking Greek ]

97
00:08:19,265 --> 00:08:21,665
<i>[ Speaking Greek ]</i>

98
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:24,065
The boy is letting them
see him.

99
00:08:24,203 --> 00:08:26,262
[ Chuckles ]
He's in plain sight !

100
00:08:26,405 --> 00:08:29,499
They do not know
if what they see is real.

101
00:08:29,642 --> 00:08:32,133
Something to do
with the mist.

102
00:08:32,278 --> 00:08:36,237
<i>Apparently, they find dangerous things,</i>
<i>spirits in the mist.</i>

103
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:41,719
The boy was being polite, giving them
time to decide if he's real.

104
00:08:41,821 --> 00:08:43,721
<i>[ Slurping Loudly ]</i>

105
00:08:52,732 --> 00:08:55,929
<i>[ Man Speaking Greek ]</i>

106
00:09:02,608 --> 00:09:04,599
[ Blowing Nose ]

107
00:09:16,322 --> 00:09:19,314
<i>[ Men Shouting ]</i>

108
00:09:19,425 --> 00:09:23,987
<i>[ Man Shouting In Native Language ]</i>

109
00:09:24,096 --> 00:09:26,462
<i>[ Man Shouting In Native Language ]</i>

110
00:09:33,205 --> 00:09:36,504
<i>[ Chattering In Native Language ]</i>

111
00:09:36,609 --> 00:09:38,076
<i>He's a messenger.</i>

112
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:41,611
He comes from their homeland
in the north with a message for Buliwyf.

113
00:09:45,217 --> 00:09:47,981
<i>He is Wulfgar,</i>

114
00:09:48,087 --> 00:09:52,547
<i>son of King Hrothgar,</i>
<i>a great king from the north.</i>

115
00:09:52,658 --> 00:09:56,116
<i>He comes to ask Buliwyf</i>
<i>for help.</i>

116
00:09:56,228 --> 00:09:59,994
<i>His father's kingdom is under attack.</i>
<i>Their village is destroyed.</i>

117
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:05,298
<i>They are menaced</i>
<i>by an ancient evil, a terror.</i>

118
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,906
<i>A terror that has no name.</i>

119
00:10:08,007 --> 00:10:11,875
<i>A terror that must not</i>
<i>be named.</i>

120
00:10:11,978 --> 00:10:13,878
<i>[ Men Murmuring ]</i>

121
00:10:17,149 --> 00:10:21,017
Look at them. What thing
would affect them so ?

122
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,588
[ Speaking Greek ]

123
00:10:26,025 --> 00:10:28,687
<i>''The name cannot be said. ''</i>

124
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:31,024
<i>[ Men Speaking Native Language ]</i>

125
00:10:33,899 --> 00:10:36,629
" He calls for
the Angel of Death.

126
00:10:36,769 --> 00:10:39,670
<i>[ Woman Speaking Native Language ]</i>

127
00:10:45,578 --> 00:10:48,445
[ Woman Continues In Native Language ]

128
00:10:51,283 --> 00:10:53,808
<i>[ Whispering ]</i>

129
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:56,911
" He calls for the bones.
She's an oracle.

130
00:10:57,023 --> 00:10:58,923
[ Woman Continues ]

131
00:11:02,895 --> 00:11:04,988
[ Woman Shouting In Native Language ]

132
00:11:09,368 --> 00:11:11,836
She calls for men,
a number of them.

133
00:11:11,904 --> 00:11:14,065
[ Speaking Greek ]

134
00:11:14,206 --> 00:11:17,698
Thirteen.
The number of months in the year.

135
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:20,073
She says 1 3 men must go."

136
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:22,340
<i>[ Buliwyf Speaking Native Language ]</i>

137
00:11:22,448 --> 00:11:25,906
[ Woman Continues ]

138
00:11:26,018 --> 00:11:27,679
<i>[ Man Speaking Native Language ]</i>

139
00:11:30,389 --> 00:11:32,983
[ Voices Overlapping ]

140
00:11:33,092 --> 00:11:34,992
[ Shouting ]

141
00:11:35,094 --> 00:11:38,757
- [ Speaking Native Language ]
-<i>[ Men Cheering ]</i>

142
00:11:38,864 --> 00:11:41,924
<i>[ Woman Continues Shouting ]</i>

143
00:11:42,068 --> 00:11:44,536
- [ Speaking Native Language ]
-<i>[ Men Cheering ]</i>

144
00:11:44,637 --> 00:11:47,538
<i>[ Woman Continues ]</i>

145
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:51,235
-<i>[ Speaking Native Language ]</i>
-<i>[ Men Cheering ]</i>

146
00:11:51,343 --> 00:11:54,744
-<i>[ Man Speaking Native Language ]</i>
-<i>[ Men Cheering ]</i>

147
00:11:54,847 --> 00:11:58,874
- [ Chattering In Native Language ]
-<i>[ Men Cheering ]</i>

148
00:12:01,754 --> 00:12:04,450
- [ Speaking Native Language ]
- [ Cheering ]

149
00:12:05,691 --> 00:12:07,591
Eight.

150
00:12:09,195 --> 00:12:11,663
- [ Speaking Native Language ]
- <i>Nine.</i>

151
00:12:11,764 --> 00:12:14,289
<i>[ Men Chattering, Laughing ]</i>

152
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:18,196
- [ Speaking Native Language ]
- [ Cheering ]

153
00:12:18,337 --> 00:12:20,737
Ten.

154
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,671
<i>[ Woman Shouting ]</i>

155
00:12:23,943 --> 00:12:26,969
[ Speaking Native Language ]

156
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:28,979
-<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>
- <i>Eleven.</i>

157
00:12:32,985 --> 00:12:36,045
- [ Speaking Native Language ]
-<i>[ Men Cheering ]</i>

158
00:12:36,155 --> 00:12:39,818
- <i>Twelve.</i>
-<i>[ Woman Shouting ]</i>

159
00:12:49,869 --> 00:12:51,837
<i>[ Man Speaking Native Language ]</i>

160
00:12:51,971 --> 00:12:55,407
- <i>[ Man #2 Speaking Native Language ]</i>
- <i>[ Man #3 Shouting ]</i>

161
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:02,342
<i>[ Buliwyf Speaking Native Language ]</i>

162
00:13:09,188 --> 00:13:12,589
" She says the 1 3th man
must be no Northman."

163
00:13:19,932 --> 00:13:22,264
What the hell
are you saying ?

164
00:13:22,401 --> 00:13:24,801
The 1 3th warrior is you.

165
00:13:30,709 --> 00:13:32,609
[ Whinnies ]

166
00:13:32,711 --> 00:13:35,771
[ Sputtering ]

167
00:13:38,017 --> 00:13:42,181
- [ Imitating Dog Barking ]
- [ Whinnies ]

168
00:13:42,288 --> 00:13:45,689
[ Chuckles, Speaking Native Language ]

169
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:48,259
<i>[ Melchisidek ] He thinks</i>
<i>your horse is too small.</i>

170
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:51,022
-<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>
- [ Speaking Greek ]

171
00:13:51,130 --> 00:13:55,396
<i>Something about, ''Only an Arab</i>
<i>would bring a dog to war. ''</i>

172
00:14:00,306 --> 00:14:02,365
" He wishes to know
your name."

173
00:14:03,709 --> 00:14:08,237
I am Ahmed Ibn Fahdlan,
Ibn Al Abbas, Ibn Rasid--

174
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:10,440
- " Eban."
- <i>No, no.</i>

175
00:14:10,549 --> 00:14:15,282
Listen. Ahmed Ibn Fahdlan.
Ibn means " son of."

176
00:14:15,387 --> 00:14:16,877
Eban.

177
00:14:16,989 --> 00:14:19,457
Hyah ! Hup !

178
00:14:25,598 --> 00:14:27,327
What is he saying ?

179
00:14:27,433 --> 00:14:30,960
" Hurry to meet death
before your place is taken."

180
00:14:32,104 --> 00:14:34,265
[ Scoffs ]

181
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:49,851
[ Melchisidek ] I will not forget you.
Go with God.

182
00:14:49,955 --> 00:14:51,855
You listening ?

183
00:15:10,643 --> 00:15:13,544
<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>

184
00:15:18,484 --> 00:15:20,884
<i>[ Chattering In Native Language ]</i>

185
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:26,155
<i>[ Laughing, Chattering Continue ]</i>

186
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:36,929
<i>[ Chattering In Native Language</i>
<i>Continues ]</i>

187
00:16:00,326 --> 00:16:03,261
<i>[ Laughing Continues ]</i>

188
00:16:03,362 --> 00:16:05,330
<i>[ Rainfall ]</i>

189
00:16:05,431 --> 00:16:07,797
<i>[ Chattering In Native Language</i>
<i>Continues ]</i>

190
00:16:09,435 --> 00:16:11,403
-<i>[ Laughing Continues ]</i>
- [ No Audio ]

191
00:16:11,503 --> 00:16:13,403
[ Speaking Native Language ]
...tomorrow.

192
00:16:13,505 --> 00:16:16,997
- [ Speaking Native Language ]
- [ No Audio ]

193
00:16:17,142 --> 00:16:21,545
<i>...sneak up to steal</i>
<i>ten or twelve horses.</i>

194
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:24,115
<i>[ Speaking Native Language ]</i>

195
00:16:30,389 --> 00:16:32,789
<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>

196
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:40,029
<i>[ Speaking Native Language ]</i>
<i>...we can find some geese.</i>

197
00:16:40,132 --> 00:16:43,659
<i>So then he says, [ Raspy Voice ]</i>
<i>''Do not foretell me wife,</i>

198
00:16:43,802 --> 00:16:47,203
for I will get to know so-proven
aye komin home tonight."

199
00:16:47,306 --> 00:16:50,332
-<i>[ Halga ] I don't sound like that.</i>
-<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>

200
00:16:51,643 --> 00:16:55,704
<i>Roneth slept with her</i>
<i>while we took the horses.</i>

201
00:16:55,814 --> 00:16:58,476
-<i>[ Laughing Continues ]</i>
-<i>[ Man ] Blowhards, both of you.</i>

202
00:16:58,584 --> 00:17:02,076
She probably was
some smoke-colored camp girl.

203
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:04,087
Looked like
that one's mother.

204
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:06,987
<i>[ Laughing Continues ]</i>

205
00:17:07,092 --> 00:17:08,992
My mother...

206
00:17:09,094 --> 00:17:11,289
<i>[ Laughing Stops ]</i>

207
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:16,991
was a pure woman...

208
00:17:20,406 --> 00:17:24,843
<i>from a noble family.</i>

209
00:17:24,977 --> 00:17:26,945
<i>And I,</i>

210
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:29,446
<i>at least,</i>

211
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:32,108
know who my father is,

212
00:17:33,318 --> 00:17:35,445
<i>you...</i>

213
00:17:37,423 --> 00:17:40,290
pig-eating
son of a whore.

214
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:42,326
<i>[ Man ] No, no, no, no, no!</i>
<i>Wait!</i>

215
00:17:42,428 --> 00:17:44,328
Come on, come on, come on,
come on. Come.

216
00:17:44,430 --> 00:17:49,390
- Come on.
- Where did you learn our language ?

217
00:17:51,270 --> 00:17:53,329
I listened !

218
00:17:55,774 --> 00:17:58,436
[ Laughing ]

219
00:18:00,979 --> 00:18:03,277
[ Laughing Continues ]

220
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:18,829
[ Whinnies ]

221
00:18:19,998 --> 00:18:23,399
You can draw... sounds ?

222
00:18:25,838 --> 00:18:27,863
" Draw sounds" ?

223
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:34,068
Yes, I can draw sounds,

224
00:18:35,848 --> 00:18:39,079
and I can speak them back.

225
00:18:39,184 --> 00:18:41,118
Show me.

226
00:18:51,396 --> 00:18:55,594
<i>There is only one God...</i>

227
00:18:57,169 --> 00:19:01,731
and Muhammad is His prophet.

228
00:19:11,517 --> 00:19:13,417
-<i>[ Man ] Bring me those sacks.</i>
- [ Whinnies ]

229
00:19:13,519 --> 00:19:15,680
- Hey !
- Mind yourself.

230
00:19:15,787 --> 00:19:18,415
[ Whispers ]
Be quiet.

231
00:19:18,524 --> 00:19:22,016
Only an " Arob" ...
would bring--

232
00:19:22,127 --> 00:19:24,721
A dog to war ?

233
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:26,730
I heard this
the first time.

234
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:30,427
-<i>[ Man Imitating Dog Barking ]</i>
-<i>[ Man Laughing ]</i>

235
00:19:32,237 --> 00:19:34,899
<i>[ Laughing Continues ]</i>

236
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:37,975
-<i>[ Barking Continues ]</i>
-<i>[ Man Imitating Dog Howling ]</i>

237
00:19:46,885 --> 00:19:49,820
[ Chuckling ]
Good going, " Arabe."

238
00:20:10,509 --> 00:20:12,568
[ Whinnying ]

239
00:20:12,678 --> 00:20:14,908
- [ Grunts ]
-<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>

240
00:20:15,013 --> 00:20:18,574
- Come on.
-<i>[ Laughing Continues ]</i>

241
00:20:27,559 --> 00:20:31,655
- The dog can jump.
- [ Men Chuckling ]

242
00:20:32,864 --> 00:20:35,765
[ Both Laughing ]

243
00:20:47,012 --> 00:20:48,912
Here.

244
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:52,710
- No, no.
- Eat !

245
00:21:00,025 --> 00:21:02,585
Shouldn't we stay
closer to land ?

246
00:21:02,694 --> 00:21:06,596
<i>No, boy! This is no day</i>
<i>to be close to land!</i>

247
00:21:20,245 --> 00:21:23,840
<i>Odin!</i>

248
00:21:35,193 --> 00:21:39,186
Odin !

249
00:21:46,371 --> 00:21:50,535
<i>Odin!</i>

250
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:53,474
Down.

251
00:21:58,950 --> 00:22:02,283
- What did you-- What is that--
- [ Whispers ] Be silent.

252
00:22:04,256 --> 00:22:07,555
Odin !

253
00:22:18,437 --> 00:22:20,462
Land !

254
00:22:20,605 --> 00:22:23,506
<i>[ Sea Gulls Cawing ]</i>

255
00:22:27,279 --> 00:22:29,179
[ Whinnying ]

256
00:22:31,149 --> 00:22:34,516
<i>'Arabe, ''speak what I draw.</i>

257
00:22:40,592 --> 00:22:43,720
There is only one God...

258
00:22:43,829 --> 00:22:46,730
and Muhammad is his...

259
00:22:52,437 --> 00:22:54,337
prophet.

260
00:22:59,945 --> 00:23:02,345
Go.

261
00:23:04,516 --> 00:23:06,416
Here.

262
00:23:06,518 --> 00:23:08,418
- You'll need this.
- [ Grunts ]

263
00:23:10,822 --> 00:23:12,722
I cannot lift this.

264
00:23:12,824 --> 00:23:15,520
Grow stronger.

265
00:23:17,295 --> 00:23:19,195
Rider.

266
00:23:23,301 --> 00:23:25,269
Well-fed on a light mount.

267
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:30,340
Perfume.

268
00:23:30,442 --> 00:23:32,410
[ Scoffs ]
A woman.

269
00:23:32,511 --> 00:23:34,411
A herald.

270
00:23:37,149 --> 00:23:39,947
It's a silk-swaddled
messenger boy.

271
00:23:40,051 --> 00:23:42,110
Tell me your names !
Quickly !

272
00:23:42,220 --> 00:23:46,054
I am Son to Hygiliak,
called Buliwyf.

273
00:23:46,158 --> 00:23:48,319
We all know
your worthy lord.

274
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:50,395
We come on an errand
to serve him.

275
00:23:50,495 --> 00:23:53,396
My Lord Hrothgar will want
to welcome you himself.

276
00:24:43,415 --> 00:24:48,944
<i>No wall, no moat,</i>
<i>not even a presentable fence.</i>

277
00:24:49,054 --> 00:24:51,113
You couldn't keep a cow
out of this place.

278
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:04,765
<i>[ Man ] Women and children.</i>

279
00:25:04,903 --> 00:25:08,066
Barely a man
between 1 5 and 50.

280
00:25:52,918 --> 00:25:57,184
<i>My lord, this is Buliwyf,son of</i>
<i>Hygiliak, come from across the sea.</i>

281
00:25:57,289 --> 00:26:00,452
<i>I know the man.</i>
<i>I sent for him.</i>

282
00:26:00,559 --> 00:26:04,325
<i>Knew him as a boy,</i>
<i>knew his father,</i>

283
00:26:04,429 --> 00:26:07,421
and I know him now.

284
00:26:07,532 --> 00:26:09,432
Grown to a man.

285
00:26:09,568 --> 00:26:13,800
<i>Grown to a fine,</i>
<i>fine man.</i>

286
00:26:23,081 --> 00:26:25,572
What troubles this place,
old man ?

287
00:26:29,454 --> 00:26:31,922
You know
he might be mad.

288
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:36,659
Be in the mist.

289
00:26:36,761 --> 00:26:39,924
<i>[ Chuckling ]</i>
<i>Has anyone seen one ?</i>

290
00:26:40,031 --> 00:26:42,329
- Has anyone seen one
in a hundred years ?
- Hyah !

291
00:26:42,434 --> 00:26:46,564
They say they used to be
all over this countryside...

292
00:26:46,705 --> 00:26:48,832
and worse further north.

293
00:26:48,974 --> 00:26:51,306
People say many things.

294
00:26:51,409 --> 00:26:55,243
Whatever they are,
unless we can track them,

295
00:26:55,347 --> 00:26:57,247
we need a proper fence
and some sort of moat--

296
00:26:57,349 --> 00:27:00,318
<i>[ Man ] We could fashion a gate</i>
<i>from a wagon.</i>

297
00:27:00,418 --> 00:27:02,477
I don't want to build a fence.
I'm not a farmer.

298
00:27:02,587 --> 00:27:06,216
- <i>Let's go track the bastards</i>--
-<i>[ Ahmed ] Gentlemen!</i>

299
00:27:22,841 --> 00:27:24,741
[ Grunts ]

300
00:27:29,381 --> 00:27:32,282
<i>[ Child Sobbing ]</i>

301
00:27:36,955 --> 00:27:39,423
- <i>Boy! Speak to me, boy!</i>
- Who did this ?

302
00:27:39,524 --> 00:27:42,425
- <i>Speak to me!</i>
- Find someone who knows him.
- Wait !

303
00:27:42,527 --> 00:27:44,586
<i>[ Sobbing Continues ]</i>

304
00:27:44,696 --> 00:27:46,596
I know him.

305
00:27:53,038 --> 00:27:55,438
It's a farmstead,
just up the glen.

306
00:27:55,540 --> 00:27:57,440
I will take you.

307
00:29:10,548 --> 00:29:13,574
Don't step
in front of me.

308
00:29:43,681 --> 00:29:45,581
[ Whining ]

309
00:29:49,687 --> 00:29:52,588
<i>[ Insects Buzzing ]</i>

310
00:30:36,201 --> 00:30:39,102
[ Wretching ]

311
00:30:42,173 --> 00:30:44,073
So it's true.

312
00:30:45,376 --> 00:30:48,174
<i>No horse tracks.</i>

313
00:30:48,279 --> 00:30:51,180
- <i>They were afoot.</i>
- <i>Their heads are missing.</i>

314
00:30:52,884 --> 00:30:56,183
<i>The child must have crawled</i>
<i>into a hole to escape.</i>

315
00:30:56,287 --> 00:31:00,018
They have been...

316
00:31:00,058 --> 00:31:01,958
gnawed upon.

317
00:31:03,061 --> 00:31:06,553
It is said
they eat the dead.

318
00:31:08,333 --> 00:31:12,861
Wh-What kind of a man...
could do that ?

319
00:31:14,439 --> 00:31:16,498
It was not man.

320
00:31:16,641 --> 00:31:18,541
- It's the Wendol.
- Shh !

321
00:31:18,643 --> 00:31:20,770
They are here.

322
00:31:25,216 --> 00:31:27,116
[ Spits ]

323
00:31:28,186 --> 00:31:30,086
What is it ?

324
00:31:30,188 --> 00:31:33,021
- The mother of the Wendol.
- [ Shouts ]

325
00:31:46,871 --> 00:31:48,771
<i>[ Horse Whinnies ]</i>

326
00:31:51,142 --> 00:31:54,805
- The trail ?
- Dies in the rocks, two miles up.

327
00:31:54,913 --> 00:31:57,438
So they are clever.

328
00:31:57,548 --> 00:31:59,482
And cautious.

329
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:01,745
<i>And there's more.</i>

330
00:32:06,057 --> 00:32:09,823
To the right.
The ridge near the watchtower.

331
00:32:16,434 --> 00:32:18,334
<i>And to the south.</i>

332
00:32:18,469 --> 00:32:21,529
The edge of the trees
near the first ridgeline.

333
00:32:24,809 --> 00:32:27,539
Something drove them out.

334
00:32:27,645 --> 00:32:29,704
Put your hand down,
little brother.

335
00:32:29,814 --> 00:32:31,839
<i>I believe they watch us.</i>

336
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:33,918
<i>Even now.</i>

337
00:32:34,018 --> 00:32:36,282
If we chase ?

338
00:32:36,387 --> 00:32:38,855
- They melt.
- Will they come to us ?

339
00:32:38,923 --> 00:32:41,687
The farmers say
they come with the mist.

340
00:32:41,793 --> 00:32:44,660
So, if there's a fog,
they will come.

341
00:32:45,863 --> 00:32:51,028
We are hunted now
in our own land.

342
00:32:51,169 --> 00:32:53,797
<i>It wasn't always such.</i>

343
00:32:53,938 --> 00:32:57,203
<i>At</i> fir<i>st we thought to build,</i>
<i>to leave something,</i>

344
00:32:57,308 --> 00:32:59,674
<i>farms as far</i>
<i>as the eye could see.</i>

345
00:32:59,777 --> 00:33:03,110
-<i>[ Crickets Chirping ]</i>
-<i>[ Dog Barking ]</i>

346
00:33:04,849 --> 00:33:06,749
<i>[ Branch Crackles ]</i>

347
00:33:08,486 --> 00:33:11,478
What of the settlements
to the north and upcountry ?

348
00:33:11,589 --> 00:33:14,387
<i>Estwyck was burned.</i>

349
00:33:14,492 --> 00:33:17,928
- Two years.
- Two years... ago.

350
00:33:19,063 --> 00:33:22,931
<i>And the others,</i>
<i>we had no word.</i>

351
00:33:23,067 --> 00:33:25,592
Not for some months.

352
00:33:25,737 --> 00:33:29,002
<i>At night,</i>
<i>with the drink upon them</i>--

353
00:33:30,108 --> 00:33:32,235
You do not drink tonight ?

354
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:34,811
No, we don't drink tonight.

355
00:33:49,927 --> 00:33:52,862
But let the dawn come,

356
00:33:52,964 --> 00:33:55,228
and they see the bodies.

357
00:33:57,468 --> 00:34:03,168
This gentleman has the look of a great
warrior. No doubt he's very brave.

358
00:34:03,274 --> 00:34:05,902
But to face the Wen...

359
00:34:06,010 --> 00:34:09,002
he'll need
some amazing luck.

360
00:34:09,113 --> 00:34:11,673
Luck often enough
will save a man,

361
00:34:11,783 --> 00:34:13,683
if his courage hold.

362
00:34:13,785 --> 00:34:15,685
<i>That's as may be.</i>

363
00:34:15,787 --> 00:34:18,620
- Who is that man ?
- King's son.

364
00:34:18,723 --> 00:34:21,624
But wait for the Wendol
one night's time...

365
00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:24,024
and then talk to us
of courage.

366
00:34:24,128 --> 00:34:28,428
I thank the lord
for his advice,

367
00:34:28,533 --> 00:34:32,230
though I don't recall
hearing any exploits of his...

368
00:34:32,370 --> 00:34:34,565
apart from killing
his brothers.

369
00:34:36,874 --> 00:34:38,774
<i>[ King ] You sit down</i>
<i>and be silent!</i>

370
00:34:38,876 --> 00:34:42,869
These are guests
at what is still my table !

371
00:34:49,287 --> 00:34:52,950
[ Guests Murmuring ]

372
00:34:59,063 --> 00:35:03,159
There is a man
who was at Estwyck.

373
00:35:03,301 --> 00:35:06,668
I saw the thing
that did this clear enough !

374
00:35:06,771 --> 00:35:10,298
Teeth like a lion,
head like a bear,

375
00:35:10,441 --> 00:35:13,706
claws that could tear
a plank to kindling.

376
00:35:13,811 --> 00:35:16,541
<i>They come in the night,</i>
<i>in the mist.</i>

377
00:35:16,647 --> 00:35:19,616
Always in the darkest, like they
could see in the black.

378
00:35:19,717 --> 00:35:22,686
Did they go on two legs
or four ?

379
00:35:22,787 --> 00:35:27,019
It seems they did both, like a thing
that was both man and bear.

380
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:30,458
<i>Though, myself,</i>
<i>I cannot tell.</i>

381
00:35:30,561 --> 00:35:33,086
I saw the glowworm, though.

382
00:35:33,197 --> 00:35:36,064
Saw it clear.
We all did on the last night.

383
00:35:36,167 --> 00:35:40,831
<i>Saw it come down out of the hills,</i>
<i>through the mist.</i>

384
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:45,306
<i>Slithering this way and that.</i>
<i>Long as a hundred ships.</i>

385
00:35:45,409 --> 00:35:48,276
<i>Spitting</i> fir<i>e at us</i>
<i>as it came.</i>

386
00:35:48,379 --> 00:35:50,904
My father's father
always warned of it.

387
00:35:51,015 --> 00:35:53,415
Said it was a hate
from old times.

388
00:35:53,518 --> 00:35:55,418
There will be fog.

389
00:35:59,390 --> 00:36:02,518
- [ Whispering ]
- <i>Bring me my armour!</i>

390
00:36:04,061 --> 00:36:06,120
I will stand
the watch with you.

391
00:36:07,899 --> 00:36:11,391
My lord, the children
will need protection.

392
00:36:11,536 --> 00:36:14,733
Should they pass us,
then you and yours must stop them.

393
00:36:22,847 --> 00:36:24,644
<i>[ Men Shouting ]</i>

394
00:36:31,789 --> 00:36:33,689
Luck in battle, boy.

395
00:36:39,096 --> 00:36:40,996
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

396
00:36:42,867 --> 00:36:46,030
<i>[ Ahmed ] How can you sleep</i>
<i>at a time like this ?</i>

397
00:36:46,170 --> 00:36:50,334
The Old Father wound the skeane
of your life a long time ago.

398
00:36:50,441 --> 00:36:53,342
Go and hide in a hole
if you wish.

399
00:36:53,444 --> 00:36:56,174
<i>But you won't live</i>
<i>one instant longer.</i>

400
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:58,180
<i>Your fate is fixed.</i>

401
00:36:58,282 --> 00:37:01,080
Fear profits
man nothing.

402
00:37:11,495 --> 00:37:14,328
<i>[ Man Snoring ]</i>

403
00:37:23,074 --> 00:37:25,975
-<i>[ Snoring Continues ]</i>
- [ Gasps ]

404
00:37:31,515 --> 00:37:34,313
[ Gasping ]

405
00:37:37,521 --> 00:37:40,183
<i>[ Distant Rustling ]</i>

406
00:37:50,301 --> 00:37:52,428
<i>[ Wood Creaking ]</i>

407
00:37:59,610 --> 00:38:02,670
<i>[ Creaking Continues ]</i>

408
00:38:05,650 --> 00:38:08,050
<i>[ Whispering ]</i>
<i>When they come,</i>

409
00:38:08,152 --> 00:38:10,950
we form a circle
in the center of the room,

410
00:38:11,055 --> 00:38:13,649
backs to one another.

411
00:38:13,758 --> 00:38:15,658
[ Whispering ]
I am not a warrior.

412
00:38:17,194 --> 00:38:20,163
Very soon you will be.

413
00:38:26,003 --> 00:38:27,903
[ Screaming ]

414
00:38:30,841 --> 00:38:32,934
[ Men Grunting ]

415
00:38:38,816 --> 00:38:41,046
[ Screeches ]

416
00:38:41,152 --> 00:38:43,484
[ Shouts ]

417
00:38:43,587 --> 00:38:45,487
<i>[ Gasps ]</i>

418
00:38:50,661 --> 00:38:52,561
<i>Ow!</i>

419
00:38:54,065 --> 00:38:56,329
[ Groans ]

420
00:38:57,635 --> 00:39:00,536
- [ Growling ]
- [ Screams ]

421
00:39:03,474 --> 00:39:05,374
<i>[ Yelling ]</i>

422
00:39:08,479 --> 00:39:10,071
[ Screaming ]

423
00:39:10,181 --> 00:39:12,581
[ Bones Cracking ]

424
00:39:33,104 --> 00:39:36,164
[ Men Panting ]

425
00:39:46,751 --> 00:39:48,685
Well, he didn't run !

426
00:39:51,889 --> 00:39:54,050
Hey.

427
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:57,985
You appear
none the worse for wear.

428
00:39:58,095 --> 00:40:01,030
- Rognar is here.
- His head ?

429
00:40:01,132 --> 00:40:03,464
No.

430
00:40:03,601 --> 00:40:07,196
They take the heads.
They always take the heads.

431
00:40:07,338 --> 00:40:09,238
<i>What about Hyglak ?</i>

432
00:40:11,308 --> 00:40:13,208
It's the same.

433
00:40:13,310 --> 00:40:15,574
- <i>I see none of them.</i>
- <i>What ?</i>

434
00:40:15,679 --> 00:40:18,011
None of them.

435
00:40:18,115 --> 00:40:20,345
None of the ones
we killed.

436
00:40:22,186 --> 00:40:24,677
Nor do I.

437
00:40:25,956 --> 00:40:27,856
Not one.

438
00:40:27,958 --> 00:40:31,689
I took two at least
that could not have lived.

439
00:40:31,796 --> 00:40:34,629
<i>As did I.</i>
<i>As did we all.</i>

440
00:40:34,732 --> 00:40:38,463
- Even the Arab gutted one.
- There was some life left in him.

441
00:40:38,602 --> 00:40:40,502
<i>They carried them off.</i>
<i>They must have.</i>

442
00:40:40,604 --> 00:40:43,095
They are demons.

443
00:40:43,240 --> 00:40:46,437
Their blood
looks real enough.

444
00:40:49,013 --> 00:40:53,109
- Ow !
- You complain much.

445
00:40:53,217 --> 00:40:54,775
[ Quietly ]
Ow.

446
00:40:54,885 --> 00:40:57,820
<i>Help me carry Ragnar out.</i>

447
00:41:02,193 --> 00:41:05,856
-<i>[ Man Groaning ]</i>
- What is that ?

448
00:41:05,963 --> 00:41:08,864
Cow urine.

449
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:10,866
" Cow urine" ?
[ Chuckles ]

450
00:41:11,001 --> 00:41:12,969
- Boiled down.
- [ Chuckles ] No.

451
00:41:13,070 --> 00:41:16,130
No, no, no. Don't put
that filth on me. No, no.

452
00:41:16,273 --> 00:41:19,333
Water.
Clean water.

453
00:41:21,278 --> 00:41:23,974
As you wish.

454
00:41:24,081 --> 00:41:27,312
Tomorrow the pus will run
and you'll have a fever.

455
00:41:33,757 --> 00:41:35,657
<i>Come, friend.</i>

456
00:41:37,995 --> 00:41:41,158
Your head has gone
looking for your hands.

457
00:41:41,265 --> 00:41:43,290
They will meet you
in paradise.

458
00:41:43,400 --> 00:41:47,837
<i>No bodies,</i>
<i>but here perhaps...</i>

459
00:41:47,938 --> 00:41:50,202
is one of their claws.

460
00:41:53,944 --> 00:41:55,844
<i>Let's go,</i>
<i>little brother.</i>

461
00:41:55,946 --> 00:41:58,073
We have the fences
to build.

462
00:42:00,050 --> 00:42:01,950
<i>[ Man Speaking, Indistinct ]</i>

463
00:42:02,019 --> 00:42:03,919
Keep 'em comin' down.

464
00:42:04,021 --> 00:42:07,286
Come in here.
Line up there.

465
00:42:07,391 --> 00:42:11,020
<i>Over here.</i>
<i>It'll be a long day.</i>

466
00:42:11,128 --> 00:42:12,618
You, in here.
You, over here.

467
00:42:14,231 --> 00:42:16,995
<i>[ Commands Continue, Indistinct ]</i>

468
00:42:25,242 --> 00:42:27,142
- [ Grunting ]
- Move !

469
00:42:30,447 --> 00:42:33,041
[ Grunting ]

470
00:42:35,352 --> 00:42:38,549
Stand there.
I'll cut this pole.

471
00:42:38,656 --> 00:42:41,318
Keep your eye on the pole,
all right ?

472
00:42:41,425 --> 00:42:43,325
So.

473
00:42:45,696 --> 00:42:47,823
Now you do it.

474
00:42:56,307 --> 00:42:58,207
[ Grunts ]

475
00:43:07,518 --> 00:43:09,418
Aah !

476
00:43:09,520 --> 00:43:12,182
[ Groans ]

477
00:43:14,792 --> 00:43:17,386
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

478
00:43:20,464 --> 00:43:23,024
Is there a metal worker ?
[ Panting ]

479
00:43:23,167 --> 00:43:25,431
<i>A metal worker!</i>

480
00:43:46,757 --> 00:43:48,657
He insisted.

481
00:43:48,759 --> 00:43:51,785
Give an Arab a sword,
he makes a knife.

482
00:43:54,098 --> 00:43:55,998
It works.

483
00:44:02,339 --> 00:44:04,967
When you die, can I give that
to me daughter ?

484
00:44:05,075 --> 00:44:07,202
<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>

485
00:44:10,581 --> 00:44:12,981
Are you thirsty ?

486
00:44:13,083 --> 00:44:17,076
- Mead ?
- Water.

487
00:44:23,861 --> 00:44:25,761
Thank you.

488
00:44:28,699 --> 00:44:30,633
Aah !

489
00:44:30,768 --> 00:44:34,397
- Ow ! [ Breathing Heavily ]
- That's a woman's sound.

490
00:44:34,538 --> 00:44:36,665
Do that again
and you'll make it.

491
00:44:36,807 --> 00:44:39,901
- You'll heal.
- [ Groans ]

492
00:44:41,011 --> 00:44:43,980
I think my nose
is ruined.

493
00:44:44,081 --> 00:44:46,174
- A small price.
- Ow !

494
00:44:48,052 --> 00:44:49,952
[ Mutters ]

495
00:44:52,890 --> 00:44:54,790
People are very quiet
today.

496
00:44:54,892 --> 00:44:58,726
- The peasants fear you will
bring the fireworm down on us.
- What ?

497
00:44:58,829 --> 00:45:01,992
The fireworm.
The fire-serpent.

498
00:45:03,133 --> 00:45:06,625
" The fire-serpent."
[ Chuckles ]

499
00:45:06,770 --> 00:45:08,670
A dragon ?

500
00:45:09,773 --> 00:45:11,673
I do not believe
in dragons.

501
00:45:19,083 --> 00:45:21,779
Beware of Prince Wigliff.

502
00:45:21,885 --> 00:45:23,785
He poisons
the king's ear,

503
