542
00:48:36,947 --> 00:48:38,847
You must stop it.

543
00:48:44,855 --> 00:48:46,755
<i>[ Crowd Gasping ]</i>

544
00:48:46,857 --> 00:48:50,657
- He's going to get killed.
- That is possible.

545
00:48:50,761 --> 00:48:52,991
But you can't--
you can't--

546
00:49:02,739 --> 00:49:05,207
[ Murmuring Continues ]

547
00:49:09,146 --> 00:49:11,239
[ Spits, Coughs ]

548
00:49:16,620 --> 00:49:18,520
[ Grunts ]

549
00:49:21,191 --> 00:49:24,092
[ Panting ]

550
00:49:25,262 --> 00:49:27,162
<i>[ Strikes Shield Twice ]</i>

551
00:49:34,805 --> 00:49:36,932
<i>[ Fighting Resumes ]</i>

552
00:49:37,074 --> 00:49:38,769
<i>[ Crowd Gasping ]</i>

553
00:49:38,875 --> 00:49:41,275
-<i>[ Men Grunting ]</i>
-<i>[ Metal Clanging ]</i>

554
00:49:53,957 --> 00:49:55,857
[ Gasps ]

555
00:49:57,461 --> 00:49:59,452
[ Sighs ]

556
00:50:02,366 --> 00:50:04,561
You stupid fools !

557
00:50:13,610 --> 00:50:15,771
[ All Gasping ]

558
00:50:28,959 --> 00:50:31,223
See to your friend.

559
00:50:32,829 --> 00:50:34,820
He was a brave man.

560
00:50:43,607 --> 00:50:46,542
- You--you could have
killed him at will.
- Yes ?

561
00:50:46,643 --> 00:50:50,204
- Wh-wh-why the deception ?
- Deception is the point !

562
00:50:50,313 --> 00:50:52,907
Any fool
can calculate strength.

563
00:50:53,016 --> 00:50:55,883
That one has been doing it
from the moment he saw us.

564
00:50:55,986 --> 00:50:58,887
Now he has to calculate
what he can't see.

565
00:51:01,925 --> 00:51:06,487
And fear what
he doesn't know.

566
00:51:06,596 --> 00:51:10,464
As you say,
foolish and expensive.

567
00:51:10,567 --> 00:51:14,025
We'll miss Angus tonight.
We will miss his sword.

568
00:51:40,997 --> 00:51:42,897
Edgtho ?

569
00:51:44,034 --> 00:51:45,899
Edgtho ?

570
00:51:46,036 --> 00:51:49,870
Stifle your racket.
I hear you.

571
00:51:49,973 --> 00:51:53,170
- I thought to find you in the tower.
- Yeah.

572
00:51:53,276 --> 00:51:55,608
- Why I'm not in it.
- <i>Brought your food.</i>

573
00:52:11,161 --> 00:52:14,892
<i>[ Distant Thunder ]</i>

574
00:52:18,735 --> 00:52:20,703
- It's going to rain.
-<i>Surf.</i>

575
00:52:20,804 --> 00:52:23,773
Three miles up
there's a cliff.

576
00:52:23,874 --> 00:52:27,139
Tide's right,
waves make thunder.

577
00:52:27,244 --> 00:52:29,940
<i>Farmers call it</i>
<i>the ''thunder cliffs. ''</i>

578
00:52:35,452 --> 00:52:37,920
<i>The mist is forming.</i>

579
00:52:38,021 --> 00:52:39,921
<i>I see it.</i>

580
00:52:49,766 --> 00:52:52,496
<i>[ Horse Snorts ]</i>

581
00:52:52,636 --> 00:52:55,867
<i>[ Horn Blowing In Distance ]</i>

582
00:53:00,577 --> 00:53:03,603
<i>The worm.</i>
<i>They've roused the</i> fir<i>eworm.</i>

583
00:53:06,917 --> 00:53:09,818
<i>[ Drums Beating ]</i>

584
00:53:12,422 --> 00:53:15,323
[ Gong Sounding ]

585
00:53:15,425 --> 00:53:17,757
<i>[ Gong Continues ]</i>

586
00:53:19,563 --> 00:53:21,463
[ Shouting ]

587
00:53:23,667 --> 00:53:26,397
[ Neighing ]

588
00:53:28,171 --> 00:53:30,435
Quickly !

589
00:53:30,540 --> 00:53:33,202
No time to waste.
Outside ! Go !

590
00:53:33,310 --> 00:53:35,210
Quickly ! Move !

591
00:53:41,718 --> 00:53:44,118
Come on !

592
00:53:55,165 --> 00:53:57,395
<i>[ Man ] Go get the water.</i>

593
00:54:01,504 --> 00:54:03,995
A serpent of fire.

594
00:54:04,140 --> 00:54:06,040
<i>Breathing</i> fir<i>e.</i>

595
00:54:06,142 --> 00:54:08,337
What's that in the field
below the tower ?

596
00:54:12,015 --> 00:54:15,280
- It's a child.
- Look at her.

597
00:54:21,825 --> 00:54:23,725
Open the gate.
Get the gate !

598
00:54:23,827 --> 00:54:26,421
- Open the gate !
- Push !

599
00:54:26,529 --> 00:54:29,464
No ! You need to raise
the spikes first ! Help me !

600
00:54:29,566 --> 00:54:32,296
- Come on !
- Down.

601
00:54:34,237 --> 00:54:36,364
[ Whinnying ]

602
00:54:46,249 --> 00:54:48,649
[ Whinnying ]

603
00:54:50,287 --> 00:54:53,916
[ Pounding Hoofbeats ]

604
00:54:54,024 --> 00:54:56,151
[ Whinnying ]

605
00:55:12,575 --> 00:55:14,600
Push it now !

606
00:55:14,711 --> 00:55:16,645
Heave !

607
00:55:20,583 --> 00:55:23,381
So you saw
the fireworm ?

608
00:55:23,486 --> 00:55:26,114
It's cavalry.

609
00:55:26,222 --> 00:55:28,952
- I rather prefer a dragon.
- Hundreds.

610
00:55:29,059 --> 00:55:31,619
<i>With torches.</i>

611
00:55:32,762 --> 00:55:34,662
Take the north.

612
00:55:34,764 --> 00:55:37,665
Let's go, little brother.
It's beginning.

613
00:55:40,403 --> 00:55:42,303
" Arabe" ! Here !

614
00:55:48,111 --> 00:55:50,511
[ Shouting ]

615
00:55:58,455 --> 00:56:00,286
Guard !

616
00:56:28,418 --> 00:56:32,354
Allah,
be merciful.

617
00:56:37,660 --> 00:56:40,060
[ Horse Whinnies ]

618
00:56:44,968 --> 00:56:47,937
[ Pounding Hoofbeats ]

619
00:57:43,326 --> 00:57:45,453
<i>Ja! Did you see that ?</i>
<i>Hold this.</i>

620
00:57:45,562 --> 00:57:48,395
I got you !
Ja !

621
00:57:51,601 --> 00:57:54,536
[ Groans ]

622
00:58:07,817 --> 00:58:10,718
[ Whinnying ]

623
00:58:10,820 --> 00:58:14,085
[ Laughing ]
Yeah !

624
00:58:16,826 --> 00:58:19,090
[ Growling ]

625
00:58:19,195 --> 00:58:21,561
[ Grunting ]

626
00:58:21,664 --> 00:58:24,895
[ Groaning ]

627
00:58:37,313 --> 00:58:40,146
[ Growling ]

628
00:58:41,718 --> 00:58:44,118
[ Growling ]

629
00:58:44,220 --> 00:58:46,780
<i>[ Groaning ]</i>

630
00:58:48,157 --> 00:58:51,149
[ Groans ]

631
00:58:51,294 --> 00:58:53,558
It's a man.

632
00:58:56,432 --> 00:58:59,060
It's a man.

633
00:58:59,202 --> 00:59:02,797
It's a man.
It's a man.

634
00:59:02,939 --> 00:59:05,965
It's a man !
It's a man !

635
00:59:08,411 --> 00:59:10,971
It's all right,
little brother.

636
00:59:11,080 --> 00:59:14,982
- There are more.
- [ Growling ]

637
00:59:15,084 --> 00:59:17,279
Aah !

638
00:59:18,855 --> 00:59:20,789
Aah !

639
00:59:20,890 --> 00:59:23,791
- Aah !
- Aah !

640
00:59:23,893 --> 00:59:25,793
Aah !

641
00:59:25,895 --> 00:59:28,625
Aah !

642
00:59:34,804 --> 00:59:37,500
- [ Whinnying ]
- Get 'em over !

643
00:59:44,414 --> 00:59:46,314
Aah !

644
00:59:47,850 --> 00:59:50,546
They've breeched the gate !

645
00:59:56,726 --> 00:59:58,250
Aah !

646
01:00:06,369 --> 01:00:09,270
[ Groaning ]

647
01:00:12,775 --> 01:00:14,709
[ Groaning ]

648
01:00:21,184 --> 01:00:23,015
Aah !

649
01:00:23,119 --> 01:00:25,087
They've breeched the gate !

650
01:00:25,188 --> 01:00:28,555
Fight them !
Turn and fight them !

651
01:00:31,094 --> 01:00:32,994
Aah !

652
01:00:34,864 --> 01:00:37,332
Come on !
Come on !

653
01:00:38,635 --> 01:00:40,535
Ahmed !

654
01:00:41,771 --> 01:00:43,671
What do I do with it ?

655
01:00:43,773 --> 01:00:47,504
Put your foot on it
and stand !

656
01:01:04,961 --> 01:01:07,486
- Aah !
- [ Whinnies ]

657
01:01:11,267 --> 01:01:13,963
Aah !

658
01:01:14,103 --> 01:01:16,799
[ Indistinct ]

659
01:01:16,939 --> 01:01:21,069
[ Grunting ]

660
01:01:23,146 --> 01:01:27,515
<i>[ Horn Blowing In Distance ]</i>

661
01:01:40,296 --> 01:01:42,890
Aah !

662
01:01:54,711 --> 01:01:56,611
Aah !

663
01:01:57,714 --> 01:02:01,047
[ Panting ]
Don't !

664
01:02:04,754 --> 01:02:07,814
[ Grunting ]

665
01:02:07,924 --> 01:02:10,392
<i>[ Horse Whinnies ]</i>

666
01:02:17,633 --> 01:02:20,193
Aah !

667
01:02:28,211 --> 01:02:30,611
[ Panting ]

668
01:03:02,345 --> 01:03:05,576
Skeld, Halga, Roneth...

669
01:03:07,216 --> 01:03:09,616
and Rethel will be
joining them.

670
01:03:21,597 --> 01:03:23,497
I cannot...

671
01:03:23,599 --> 01:03:27,296
taste neither
the fermentation of grape...

672
01:03:29,038 --> 01:03:31,404
nor of wheat.

673
01:03:31,507 --> 01:03:35,204
- [ Chuckles, Laughs ]
- What ?

674
01:03:35,311 --> 01:03:37,541
Why do you
laugh ?

675
01:03:41,350 --> 01:03:44,444
Honey.
[ Laughs ]

676
01:03:44,554 --> 01:03:47,284
It's made from honey.

677
01:04:20,256 --> 01:04:22,486
We will die here.

678
01:04:25,027 --> 01:04:26,927
It is...

679
01:04:29,265 --> 01:04:31,165
possible.

680
01:04:50,319 --> 01:04:52,913
Come.

681
01:05:02,932 --> 01:05:04,832
Come on.

682
01:05:07,870 --> 01:05:10,771
She finish you,
or bring you back to life ?

683
01:05:10,873 --> 01:05:13,535
A gentleman doesn't
discuss such things.

684
01:05:17,480 --> 01:05:19,880
- [ Growls ]
- <i>Three more on the fence.</i>

685
01:05:28,691 --> 01:05:31,524
Looks like the mating
of a man and some beast.

686
01:05:31,627 --> 01:05:33,925
It's a man.

687
01:05:35,531 --> 01:05:37,863
<i>If it's a man,</i>
<i>it must sleep.</i>

688
01:05:38,000 --> 01:05:41,128
If it sleeps, it has a lair
and we have a trail.

689
01:05:41,270 --> 01:05:43,636
Attack them ?

690
01:05:43,739 --> 01:05:46,071
Is there a choice ?

691
01:05:48,844 --> 01:05:52,371
Come with me.
There is a woman who can help.

692
01:05:58,287 --> 01:06:00,118
Bring the Arab.

693
01:06:00,222 --> 01:06:03,123
<i>There's one down here</i>
<i>who was old...</i>

694
01:06:03,225 --> 01:06:05,455
<i>when my grandmother</i>
<i>was a girl.</i>

695
01:06:05,561 --> 01:06:07,461
She's quite mad.

696
01:06:07,563 --> 01:06:09,963
The perfect advisor.

697
01:06:12,735 --> 01:06:16,831
Oh, Weilew.
Oh.

698
01:06:16,973 --> 01:06:19,441
[ Clicks Tongue ]
Shame, shame, shame.

699
01:06:19,542 --> 01:06:23,740
It's a Queen Weilew fronts
me now, does she not ?

700
01:06:23,846 --> 01:06:26,076
We seek your counsel,
Madam.

701
01:06:26,182 --> 01:06:28,173
We or he ?

702
01:06:28,284 --> 01:06:30,844
Step closer, Buliwyf.

703
01:06:32,188 --> 01:06:34,782
<i>Closer.</i>

704
01:06:34,890 --> 01:06:36,790
You know me ?

705
01:06:36,892 --> 01:06:40,692
I have ears.
"Warrior," says the wind.

706
01:06:42,264 --> 01:06:44,494
<i>''Chieftain, ''</i>
<i>says the rain.</i>

707
01:06:44,600 --> 01:06:47,330
But why seek you me ?

708
01:06:47,470 --> 01:06:50,030
Met you your match ?

709
01:06:50,172 --> 01:06:53,039
Met you your match...

710
01:06:53,142 --> 01:06:55,975
<i>with the eaters of the dead?</i>

711
01:06:58,080 --> 01:06:59,980
We seek your wisdom.

712
01:07:01,650 --> 01:07:04,448
Wars are won in the will.

713
01:07:04,553 --> 01:07:07,579
Perhaps you've been fighting
in the wrong field.

714
01:07:07,690 --> 01:07:11,524
<i>Have you a token ?</i>
<i>A thing.</i>

715
01:07:11,627 --> 01:07:15,188
- A thing of them.
- Yes.

716
01:07:24,774 --> 01:07:27,004
Ahh.

717
01:07:28,711 --> 01:07:32,704
They show you the way
you will not see.

718
01:07:32,815 --> 01:07:35,978
Slaughter them
till you rot.

719
01:07:36,085 --> 01:07:38,246
<i>You'll accomplish nothing.</i>

720
01:07:39,789 --> 01:07:42,019
Find the root.

721
01:07:42,124 --> 01:07:44,183
-<i>Strike the will.</i>
- How ?

722
01:07:44,293 --> 01:07:46,853
This is the mother
of the Wen.

723
01:07:46,962 --> 01:07:50,022
She they revere.

724
01:07:50,132 --> 01:07:52,066
